## **Description**
The **Variable **operator allows to use a simple or complex accumulation variable defined in the configuration settings.

## **Input**
**Input**

**Data type**

**Description**

**#state**

Any

The node that determines the operator's state change

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Variable

The accumulation node, in case of a simple accumulation variable

## **Output**
**Output**

**Data type**

**Description**

**out0**

Any

The number of instances of the grouping of variables defined in the configuration settings

## **Settings**
**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

- Select the **Complex type variable (tree structure) **option to select the schema and define the hierarchy of the elements to link in input and output.

- Select the required data structure from the **Schema **drop-down menu. The **Choose root element **panel displays the tree structure of the selected schema; for example:![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- In the **Choose Root Element **panel, click on the row corresponding to the element that you want to use as root of the tree structure; for example: ![](data:image/png;base64,)![](data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAA8AAAATAQMAAAB1DMXpAAAABlBMVEUAAAD///+l2Z/dAAAAAWJLR0QAiAUdSAAAAAlwSFlzAAAOxAAADsQBlSsOGwAAAA5JREFUCJlj+P+PgSwEADUmJciRioiXAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC)

- Click **Apply **to confirm.

## **Special cases**
In special cases, the operator behaves as follows:

**Case**

**Behavior**

**Complex variable (hierarchical structure)**

If used, the operator groups the input and output elements.

**#state input LINKED**

If linked, the operator calculates the variable at every change of the linked input.

**#state input NOT LINKED**

If not linked, the operator calculates the variable every time that one of its nodes is used in output.
